---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="week 12 — the ratio is usually like this" description="four reads on ai tooling. one validated what already works. one taught something that was already figured out. one actually changed a workflow.">
  <div class="space-y-6">
    <div class="font-mono text-xs text-faint mb-4">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">reading</a> <span class="text-faint">/</span> week 12
    </div>

    <h1 class="font-display text-3xl font-normal animate-fade-up">the ratio is usually like this</h1>

    <div class="essay mt-10 animate-fade-up delay-1">
      <p>read four things this week about ai tooling</p>

      <p class="mt-6">one validated what already works</p>
      <p>one taught something that was already figured out</p>
      <p>one actually changed a workflow</p>
      <p class="text-dim">one was just a good primer</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">the ratio tells you something</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>boris cherny talking about how claude code gets built</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">three terminals</p>
      <p class="text-spice">three contexts</p>
      <p class="text-spice">one product</p>

      <p class="mt-6">felt less like learning</p>
      <p class="text-dim">more like recognition</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://newsletter.pragmaticengineer.com/p/building-claude-code-with-boris-cherny" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">Building Claude Code with Boris Cherny →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>mihail eric on a new era of learning software engineering</p>

      <p class="mt-6">juniors starting with ai from day one</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the framing is solid</p>

      <p class="mt-6">but after building a governance layer because agents were lying to each other</p>
      <p class="text-dim">it mostly reads like catching up</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=wEsjK3Smovw" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">From Writing Code to Managing Agents →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>the figma piece was different</p>

      <p class="mt-6">design updates spacing</p>
      <p>code doesn't know</p>
      <p class="text-crimson">drift just compounds</p>

      <p class="mt-6">now it's one prompt to sync</p>

      <p class="mt-6">not incremental</p>
      <p class="text-spice">removes an entire class of bug</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://lennysnewsletter.com/p/from-figma-to-claude-code-and-back" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">From Figma to Claude Code and back →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>ben thompson on agents over bubbles</p>

      <p class="mt-6">not a hot take</p>
      <p class="text-gold">just clean structure</p>

      <p class="mt-6">who's building what</p>
      <p>why the agent layer matters more than the model layer</p>

      <p class="mt-6"><a href="https://stratechery.com/2026/agents-over-bubbles" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-water hover:underline">Agents Over Bubbles →</a></p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p>pattern across all four</p>

      <p class="mt-6">most ai content is still framing the problem</p>

      <p class="mt-6">the value shows up in artifacts that skip that</p>
      <p class="text-spice">and just solve the workflow</p>

      <p class="mt-6">figma mcp doesn't explain why syncing matters</p>
      <p class="text-dim">it just syncs</p>

      <hr class="my-12 border-border" />

      <p class="text-gold">useful filter</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">did it change something tomorrow</p>
      <p>or describe something from last week</p>

      <p class="mt-6">most weeks it's 1 out of 4</p>

      <p class="mt-6 text-spice">the one carries the rest</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-16 pt-6 border-t border-border">
      <a href="/reading" class="text-spice hover:underline">← back to reading</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .essay p {
    line-height: 1.8;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }
</style>
